but also by Bob Siemens,

00:30:32.300 --> 00:30:34.600
who was one of his students,
who then became second in

00:30:34.600 --> 00:30:36.430
command at NASA during
the Apollo program.

00:30:36.430 --> 00:30:37.920
We'll talk about that.

00:30:37.920 --> 00:30:43.040
And was one of their first
forays into gyroscopes, which

00:30:43.040 --> 00:30:46.620
then became really important
during the Cold War and later.

00:30:46.620 --> 00:30:49.560
I keep pushing the wrong
side of the mouse.

00:30:49.560 --> 00:30:51.820
And this is actually
how it worked.

00:30:51.820 --> 00:30:56.650
So you can see they can just
see the site and it sort of

00:30:56.650 --> 00:30:59.790
